    {
        "content": "<p>So <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>U</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> are <strong>spaces over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span></strong>, meaning they'r equipped with maps to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>, though of a very particular sort.   Your equation is then saying precisely that your map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>U</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f : U \\to U'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is a <strong>map of spaces over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span></strong>.</p>",
        "id": 223994293,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611632676
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, you are describing a certain subcategory of the category of spaces over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>The category of spaces over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> is also called the <strong>slice category</strong> of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>, or (more descriptively yet tersely) the <strong><a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/over+category#definition\">over category</a></strong> of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>.    If you look at the link you'll see a commutative triangle, and this is precisely the equation you wrote down.</p>",
        "id": 223994431,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611632911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>All the business about the space <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span></span></span></span> actually being an open subset of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B \\times \\mathbb{C}^n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68889em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.664392em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is too detailed and specialized to expect category theorists to have a name for it.    <span aria-label=\"upside down\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f643\" role=\"img\" title=\"upside down\">:upside_down:</span></p>",
        "id": 223994554,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611633109
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>More precisely: there might be a name for the particular subcategory of the slice category that you care about, but I've never heard of it.</p>",
        "id": 223994603,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611633168
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span></p>",
        "id": 223994613,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1611633217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what about this business of taking a product (ignoring the open set stuff)? as in, this specific type of slice category where you fix some X and then look at the category of “things producted with X as objects living over X”. does this have a snappy name?</p>",
        "id": 223994684,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1611633310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not that I know of. To me it's just some subcategory of the slice category.   But maybe someone has made up a name for it.</p>",
        "id": 223995154,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611633978
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, I guess I'd call something like <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\times B \\to B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> a \"trivial bundle\" in some very general sense of the word \"bundle\".</p>",
        "id": 223995173,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611634028
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I guess I  might call all the full subcategory of the slice category of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> consisting of objects of the form <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\times B \\to B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> the \"category of trivial bundles over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>\", if I had to call it something.</p>",
        "id": 223995249,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611634135
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it does look rather bundle-y indeed</p>",
        "id": 223995251,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1611634138
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, a general locally trivial bundle is a bundle that's locally isomorphic to one of this \"trivial\" form.</p>",
        "id": 223995263,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611634171
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But then you're going a further step and looking at subobjects of these \"trivial bundles\"... but not <em>all</em> subobjects, just \"open\" ones...</p>",
        "id": 223995319,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611634207
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i guess i should just look up “mixed varieties” or “mixed complex spaces” up on the nlab and see if anybody has said anything there</p>",
        "id": 223995343,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1611634253
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but my go-to is now this zulip, since you get a nice chit chat with your answers <span aria-label=\"wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f609\" role=\"img\" title=\"wink\">:wink:</span></p>",
        "id": 223995357,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1611634275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just be done with it and call them Hosgood spaces.</p>",
        "id": 223995366,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1611634285
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>\"the zulip subcategory\"</p>",
        "id": 224013261,
        "sender_full_name": "fosco",
        "timestamp": 1611652548
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I assume this is intended to get at a definition of something like a family of complex manifolds over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>? Is this what a \"mixed complex space\" is?<br>\nI thought about something like this in another context recently but I didn't know if there was a name for it.</p>",
        "id": 224046293,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1611671413
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes, this is the definition that comes just before the definition of a mixed space (cf <a href=\"http://www.numdam.org/item/SHC_1960-1961__13_1_A1_0/\">http://www.numdam.org/item/SHC_1960-1961__13_1_A1_0/</a>)</p>",
        "id": 224047035,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1611671689
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>aha, I didn't translate my search queries into french...</p>",
        "id": 224047123,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1611671737
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll have to read this more closely later but this looks interesting, thanks!</p>",
        "id": 224047884,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1611672076
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(it’s next on my list of things to translate, which is why i’m trying to understand it a bit better)</p>",
